					<head>A Persian translation of part of Alf laylah wa-laylah</head>
					<msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85049710">
						<summary>A Persian translation of the first 200 nights of the <title>Alf
								laylah wa-laylah</title> (<title xml:lang="ar">الف ليلة
								وليلة</title>) translated by Murād ʻAlī Muʼaddī(?) of the ẓillah
							Allahabad. </summary>
						<msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_598-item1">
							<author key="">
								<persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Murād ʻAlī Muʼaddī</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="fa">مراد علی مؤدی </persName>
							</author>
							
							<title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="">Tarjumah-’i Alf Laylā</title>
							<title xml:lang="fa">ترجمهٔ الف ليلة </title>
							<colophon>(F. 326r) Completed on 17th July 1825 corresponding to 29
								Zu’l-Qaʻdah 1240 AH by <persName role="scr" key="">Ḥimāyat
									ʻAlī</persName> in the Shalimar garden at the request of Capt.
									<persName role="pat" key="">Stapleton</persName> and General
								Ochterlony [ie. <persName role="pat" key="viaf_69802904"
									>Major-General Sir David Ochterlony, 1758-182</persName>5]. </colophon>
							<note>
								<p>Followed on f. 327 by notes on reading and writing (در خواندن و
									نوشتن) and on f. 329 on acting justly (در انصاف کردن). </p>
							</note>
							<textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
